From the owners of Downbeat Diner, Proof Public House is a pizza pub in Downtown Honolulu with a full bar, craft beer on tap and tons of vegan options. There are rotating pizza selections every day to include a vegan, vegetarian and omnivore slice but you can also build your own pie. If you're feeling saucy ask about their vegan dipping sauces. All of their bread is made in-house: pizza crust, sandwich buns, pita bread....the whole chabang.  Proof is located in an alleyway and is a little off the beaten path of the other Chinatown spots which gives it a unique charm. It's like a secret find. The original inhabitant of the space was the historic lobby-level bar of the Blaisdell Hotel in the 1930's. Definitely recommend this spot for groups since there is something for everyone.
